 cadets  We appreciate the time they ve taken to address our cadets  On 1 February 2007  Mr  Thomas Greenspon  VMI Class of  85  spoke to 1st and 2nd classmen  Mr  Greenspon is a vice president with Booz Allen Hamilton specializing in IT strategy and systems information for the U S  Department of Defense  The subject of his talk was the importance of written and oral communication in the job market  Mr  Gil Minor  VMI Class of 1963  spoke to 1st 2nd and 3rd classmen on February 27th  The topic of his remarks was  Taking a  6 Million Private Company to a  6 Billion Public Company  Mr  Minor is the Chairman of the Board of Owens   Minor  Inc  a  5 billion Fortune 500 distributor of medical and surgical supplies to hospitals  nursing homes and physicians  the President of the VMI Board of Visitors  Dr  Lowell Catlett  the Dean of the New Mexico State University Department of Agricultural and Home Economics  visited VMI on Thursday  March 29th  In the afternoon  he engaged in a Q A with our majors regarding the 21st century economy  Later that evening  he gave an address that was both informative and entertaining to the the 2nd  3rd  and 4th class cadets as well as the 1st class ECBU majors in JM Hall  This presentation  entitled  New Frontier that Change Everything  focused on the constantly evolving US and world economy  The cadets showed their appreciation with a standing ovation  Spring 2007 Newsletter  AACSB Accreditation  Field Test BU  Mission Statement  New Faculty Faces  New Book Released  Faculty Research  Speakers  Engineering Initiative  Cadet Research  Cadet Investment Group  Cadet Internships  Class of 2005  Cadet Field Trip  Cadet Awards  Hinman Award  Stay Connected  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It